Bad Blood: A Cautionary Tale

Health-Medical Documentary published by Necessary Films in 2010 - English language


Information
------------------------------

What if your life-saving medicine contained deadly viruses - and the drug manufacturers, the government, and your own doctors knew but failed to warn you?
Through the eyes of survivors and family members, BAD BLOOD chronicles how a &quot;miracle&quot; treatment for hemophilia became an agent of death for 10,000 Americans. Faced with evidence that pharmaceutical companies and government regulators knew the product was contaminated with deadly viruses from the 1960s through the early 1990s, the hemophilia community launched a powerful and inspiring fight to right the system that failed them and to make it safer for all.

